WEBVTT

00:01.336 --> 00:02.335
<i> access your memory of that day</i>

00:02.469 --> 00:03.869
<i> through hypnosis.</i>

00:03.871 --> 00:06.205
<i> [dark music]</i>

00:06.341 --> 00:07.806
<i> You had a mother executed,</i>

00:07.808 --> 00:09.875
and now there's proof
she was not a murderer.

00:10.011 --> 00:13.346
<i> - A dog just needs</i>
<i> to know who his master is.</i>

00:13.480 --> 00:17.149
- What do you want?
- Information.

00:17.284 --> 00:19.618
<i> Another child is missing.</i>
- [cries]

00:19.620 --> 00:21.420
<i> - The doll connects</i>
<i> the two cases.</i>

00:21.556 --> 00:25.958
- EH purchased the Ruby Red
doll on four occasions.

00:26.093 --> 00:28.427
<i> There is an address.</i>
<i> - Hudson Street.</i>

00:28.429 --> 00:30.095
<i> - Goo Goo owns that place.</i>

00:30.097 --> 00:31.163
[gun clicks]

00:31.298 --> 00:32.431
<i> - Something doesn't add up.</i>

00:32.433 --> 00:34.567
<i> - Someone poisoned the baby</i>

00:34.702 --> 00:37.036
<i> and then gave the baby</i>
<i> powdered charcoal.</i>

00:37.038 --> 00:40.239
- The most common place
to find it is a maternity ward.

00:40.375 --> 00:43.242
<i> - The Lying-In Hospital.</i>

00:44.511 --> 00:46.645
[ticking]

00:46.781 --> 00:48.447
- Breathe.

00:48.583 --> 00:51.516
- [breathes shakily]

00:51.518 --> 00:53.919
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:53.921 --> 00:55.988
- Breathe.

00:56.123 --> 00:58.791
<i> [soft tense music]</i>

00:58.926 --> 01:00.059
Breathe.

01:00.194 --> 01:02.395
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:02.529 --> 01:05.398
It is not supernatural.

01:05.532 --> 01:09.935
This is a purely
physical phenomenon, Sara.

01:09.937 --> 01:11.804
You're having doubts,
and right at this moment,

01:11.939 --> 01:14.407
your conscious mind is actively
looking for a reason

01:14.541 --> 01:17.342
not to go through
with the hypnosis.

01:17.478 --> 01:19.745
- Naturally,
I have reservations,

01:19.880 --> 01:21.881
but I'm not fearful for myself.

01:22.016 --> 01:23.949
How can I ask the señora
to submit to something

01:24.085 --> 01:25.350
if I don't know what it is

01:25.486 --> 01:28.020
and whether it might
further traumatize her?

01:28.155 --> 01:29.688
- Yet to do this, Sara,

01:29.690 --> 01:32.491
you must freely and fully
embrace this experiment,

01:32.627 --> 01:33.692
without reservation.

01:33.694 --> 01:36.395
- And I do so, Laszlo.

01:37.432 --> 01:39.031
- Close your eyes.

01:39.166 --> 01:42.234
Focus on my words.

01:42.369 --> 01:46.105
Hypnos was the Greek god
of sleep.

01:46.107 --> 01:51.644
His mother, Nyx,
was the goddess of the night.

01:51.779 --> 01:56.115
His father, Erebus,
was the god of darkness.

01:56.250 --> 01:58.251
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:58.385 --> 02:02.387
Hypnos resided in a dark cave

02:02.389 --> 02:06.125
where no light was cast...

02:06.260 --> 02:09.728
not by the sun or moon...

02:09.730 --> 02:13.332
not by the sun or moon.

02:13.334 --> 02:15.334
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:15.470 --> 02:18.938
Now feel your hand.

02:19.073 --> 02:21.606
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:21.608 --> 02:25.010
Your hand feels heavy.

02:25.012 --> 02:29.414
But slowly, it begins
to feel insubstantial.

02:29.416 --> 02:31.416
Light...

02:31.418 --> 02:33.486
lighter...

02:33.620 --> 02:36.355
floating upwards,
as light as a feather,

02:36.357 --> 02:40.559
as if an invisible wire were
attached to your index finger.

02:40.695 --> 02:44.096
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:44.231 --> 02:46.832
- Such a strange feeling.

02:46.834 --> 02:49.234
<i> [mysterious music]</i>

02:49.370 --> 02:52.237
- Now I want you to go
to a calm place.

02:52.373 --> 02:54.640
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:54.775 --> 02:57.376
Of safety, happiness.

02:57.378 --> 02:59.244
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:59.246 --> 03:00.645
A time of innocence.

03:00.647 --> 03:02.447
<i> [laughter]</i>

03:02.583 --> 03:04.449
Perhaps your family home.

03:04.585 --> 03:08.521
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:08.656 --> 03:11.524
Oh.
[gasps]

03:11.658 --> 03:13.125
- What is it?

03:13.260 --> 03:18.998
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:19.133 --> 03:20.666
<i> How old are you?</i>

03:20.801 --> 03:24.269
- [breathes shakily]
12.

03:24.271 --> 03:25.338
12.

03:25.472 --> 03:27.206
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:27.208 --> 03:29.474
<i> - Where are you?</i>

03:29.610 --> 03:33.278
<i> - My family's house</i>
<i> in Rhinebeck.</i>

03:33.280 --> 03:36.415
I'm outside.
It's summer.

03:36.417 --> 03:39.018
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:39.020 --> 03:42.421
[breathing deeply]

03:42.557 --> 03:48.694
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:48.696 --> 03:49.895
<i> [gunshot]</i>

03:49.897 --> 03:50.830
Stop.

03:58.239 --> 04:00.105
[sniffles]

04:00.241 --> 04:03.142
[breathes heavily]

04:05.646 --> 04:08.513
<i> [dark music]</i>

04:08.649 --> 04:09.715
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:38.279 --> 04:41.180
[indistinct chatter]

04:43.150 --> 04:44.750
What is it?

04:44.752 --> 04:47.886
- It's the clothing
the Napp baby wore.

04:47.888 --> 04:51.223
- What's the black mark?
- Charcoal.

04:51.358 --> 04:52.958
- And blood.

04:52.960 --> 04:55.694
- It's a fine fabric,

04:55.696 --> 04:57.562
which suggests affluence,
does it not?

04:57.698 --> 05:00.032
- I believe this was made,
not purchased.

05:00.167 --> 05:03.769
Seems to be hand-stitched.
There is no label.

05:03.771 --> 05:06.772
This piping should be closer
to the hem,

05:06.774 --> 05:09.174
unless it was made
from an adult woman's skirt,

05:09.310 --> 05:10.643
a very fine one.

05:10.778 --> 05:12.978
- So not affluence,
but aspiration to affluence.

05:13.114 --> 05:16.249
The stitching is well-done.
Steady hand.

05:16.383 --> 05:19.452
Perhaps the work of a surgeon.
- Or a seamstress.

05:19.587 --> 05:21.120
- Well, there are many things
about Dr. Markoe

05:21.255 --> 05:23.588
that warrant an investigation,
but, uh--

05:23.590 --> 05:25.791
- Perhaps it is a woman.

05:25.793 --> 05:28.260
Wanting a child,
preparing for it.

05:28.395 --> 05:30.463
Or a woman who lost a child.

05:30.597 --> 05:32.197
- Is it so simple?

05:32.199 --> 05:35.134
<i> Entia non sunt multiplicanda</i>
<i> sine necessitatem.</i>

05:35.136 --> 05:38.003
- Oh, please, Laszlo.
No one speaks Latin anymore.

05:38.139 --> 05:41.674
- Entities are not to be
multiplied without necessity.

05:41.809 --> 05:43.208
- Occam's razor.

05:43.210 --> 05:45.210
- Sometimes we look
for complicated reasons

05:45.212 --> 05:47.280
when something
is often straightforward.

05:47.414 --> 05:49.548
- But why does she kill?

05:49.684 --> 05:50.816
- She's angry that other women

05:50.951 --> 05:52.017
are mothering their own
children

05:52.153 --> 05:54.619
while hers has been taken
from her.

05:54.621 --> 05:56.355
She tries to replace
the lost child,

05:56.357 --> 05:59.292
but it cannot possibly
feel the same.

05:59.426 --> 06:01.226
- A cuckoo in the nest.

06:01.228 --> 06:03.296
She loves it at first,
but then looks at it

06:03.430 --> 06:04.630
as if it were
a changeling child,

06:04.765 --> 06:06.832
which of course it is.

06:06.968 --> 06:08.301
- I found something.

06:08.435 --> 06:09.702
A way to get you access

06:09.837 --> 06:11.636
to the Lying-In Hospital
and Markoe.

06:11.638 --> 06:12.905
The hospital's a charity,

06:13.040 --> 06:14.573
so I figured they gotta
have a few parties

06:14.575 --> 06:17.776
to drum up some cash
from the rich donors, right?

06:17.778 --> 06:19.512
So the papers
will come along too.

06:19.646 --> 06:20.913
- What did you learn?

06:21.048 --> 06:22.581
- Guests included--
- Not the guests, Bitsy.

06:22.583 --> 06:24.183
The hosts.
- Oh.

06:27.054 --> 06:29.588
Havemeyer, Milbank, Hardy,

06:29.590 --> 06:32.591
Gildersleeve, Furman, Griswold.

06:32.727 --> 06:35.794
- Wait, Gildersleeve.
I know the family.

06:35.930 --> 06:37.930
I'm quite good friends
with Oggie.

06:38.065 --> 06:39.865
He's the heir to the fortune.

06:39.867 --> 06:41.934
- I believe I have invited him
to your bachelor party.

06:42.069 --> 06:44.403
- You know, Laszlo, bachelor
parties are supposed to happen

06:44.405 --> 06:48.341
sometime after the
engagement party, not before.

06:48.475 --> 06:51.677
- I imagine we could ask
Oggie Gildersleeve for a favor

06:51.812 --> 06:54.079
to get an interview
at the Lying-In Hospital.

06:54.081 --> 06:56.615
- I don't see why the hell not.

06:56.617 --> 06:59.618
<i>[stately dramatic music]</i>

06:59.754 --> 07:06.893
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:15.036 --> 07:16.836
- Sara.

07:17.838 --> 07:19.905
- [groans]
Foul!

07:19.907 --> 07:22.175
- Perfectly good touch.

07:22.309 --> 07:24.509
How did you persuade them
to let you down here?

07:24.511 --> 07:27.046
- I didn't ask.
- [sighs]

07:27.181 --> 07:29.448
Sara Howard,
this is Ogden Gildersleeve.

07:29.584 --> 07:32.785
Ogden, this is Sara Howard,
a dear family friend.

07:32.920 --> 07:35.188
- Call me Oggie, Miss Howard.

07:35.322 --> 07:36.722
- I'm quite sure
I don't know you well enough,

07:36.724 --> 07:37.790
Mr. Gildersleeve.

07:37.925 --> 07:40.193
- Well, we can, uh,
remedy that.

07:42.597 --> 07:45.464
- Did Mr. Moore inform you
that I may have a favor to ask?

07:45.600 --> 07:46.732
- [chuckles]

07:46.867 --> 07:48.867
You are uncommonly direct,
Miss Howard.

07:48.869 --> 07:50.135
- Oh, be warned, Oggie.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.870
This woman tends
to speak her mind.

07:51.872 --> 07:53.205
- I'm afraid I cannot delay.

07:53.340 --> 07:55.808
The matter is rather important.

07:55.943 --> 07:57.743
- Well, whatever it is,
Miss Howard,

07:57.878 --> 07:59.412
I'm at your disposal.

08:02.617 --> 08:05.618
<i> [ominous music]</i>

08:05.753 --> 08:12.925
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:13.761 --> 08:15.094
- Her room is ready.

08:15.096 --> 08:16.762
- I'm bringing her there now,
Dr. Markoe.

08:16.764 --> 08:18.497
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:18.633 --> 08:19.898
- Where is my baby?

08:19.900 --> 08:21.634
I want to see her.
- Yes.

08:21.769 --> 08:23.702
- Where is my baby?
- Shh, shh.

08:23.838 --> 08:25.904
Your child is with the angels
now, my dear.

08:25.906 --> 08:28.240
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:28.375 --> 08:29.041
- No.

08:29.176 --> 08:30.843
No, no, no, no, no. No!

08:30.978 --> 08:32.311
- Please.
- No, no, no!

08:32.313 --> 08:34.046
- Shh, shh.
- Please, no, no, no, no!

08:34.181 --> 08:36.115
- Matron?
- No, no, no, no!

08:36.250 --> 08:38.451
- Oh, yes.
- No, no, no, no!

08:38.586 --> 08:40.653
No.

08:40.788 --> 08:42.721
- No, please, please, no.
- [shushing]

08:42.857 --> 08:45.858
- No...
[groans]

08:45.993 --> 08:48.994
[baby crying in distance]

08:49.130 --> 08:51.731
- Take her to her room.

08:52.934 --> 08:56.001
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

08:56.003 --> 09:01.340
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:01.342 --> 09:02.275
- 2nd and 18th.

09:02.409 --> 09:05.611
Everybody off...
[continues indistinctly]

09:05.746 --> 09:08.614
<i> [ominous music]</i>

09:08.749 --> 09:11.416
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:11.552 --> 09:13.886
[baby crying in distance]

09:14.021 --> 09:20.693
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:20.828 --> 09:23.696
[crying continues]

09:23.831 --> 09:30.870
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:38.980 --> 09:42.447
[door creaking]

09:42.583 --> 09:49.488
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:59.867 --> 10:02.535
<i> [eerie music]</i>

10:02.670 --> 10:04.670
- I fell.

10:04.805 --> 10:06.471
- Can I call someone for you?

10:06.607 --> 10:08.407
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:08.543 --> 10:11.010
- Grace!

10:11.012 --> 10:14.813
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:14.949 --> 10:15.948
There you are.

10:16.083 --> 10:18.017
Come back to bed.
That's it.

10:18.019 --> 10:19.818
That's a good girl...

10:19.954 --> 10:21.954
[continues indistinctly]

10:22.089 --> 10:23.889
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:24.025 --> 10:27.426
[babies crying]

10:27.428 --> 10:31.430
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:31.566 --> 10:34.000
- [groaning]

10:37.772 --> 10:39.639
- You seem to be lost.

10:40.641 --> 10:43.242
- I seem to have taken
a wrong turn.

10:43.378 --> 10:46.379
- Come, let's give
these mommies their privacy.

10:46.513 --> 10:50.783
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:50.918 --> 10:55.054
I don't believe you told me
the nature of your visit.

10:55.056 --> 10:58.591
- I'm Sara Howard.
I've come to see Dr. Markoe.

10:58.726 --> 11:00.059
- Please.

11:00.061 --> 11:04.129
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:04.131 --> 11:06.999
- So you are a friend
of the Gildersleeves?

11:08.335 --> 11:10.936
But I feel we've met
a prior occasion, Miss Howard.

11:10.938 --> 11:13.806
- I believe you know quite well
where we met previously.

11:13.941 --> 11:15.741
- Yes, yes, I do.

11:15.743 --> 11:16.742
You were the young lady,
in fact,

11:16.877 --> 11:17.877
who tried to impede

11:18.012 --> 11:20.279
the execution
of poor Martha Napp.

11:20.415 --> 11:22.415
I take it you're here
to accuse me.

11:22.549 --> 11:25.084
- You seem unconcerned
that Martha Napp's baby

11:25.086 --> 11:26.619
was discovered after her death.

11:26.754 --> 11:30.089
- I am not unconcerned,
as you put it, Miss Howard.

11:30.091 --> 11:32.958
On the contrary,
I am at my wit's end.

11:33.094 --> 11:35.761
I see young girls
like Martha Napp all the time.

11:35.896 --> 11:38.563
Poor, uneducated,
easily preyed upon.

11:38.699 --> 11:41.300
Often, the child is not wanted,
and harm is done to it.

11:41.302 --> 11:43.902
It is regrettably
not an uncommon experience.

11:43.904 --> 11:45.170
- If you don't mind,
Dr. Markoe,

11:45.306 --> 11:46.639
I prefer to deal in specifics

11:46.774 --> 11:48.173
rather than generalities.

11:48.309 --> 11:50.309
To speak candidly,
Martha Napp's baby was poisoned

11:50.445 --> 11:53.112
with a drug found only
in hospitals such as yours.

11:54.181 --> 11:56.181
- [sighs]

11:56.317 --> 11:59.318
It is a terrible business,
I grant you.

11:59.320 --> 12:02.187
But as to the facts,
they are lamentably scarce.

12:02.189 --> 12:04.523
- Certainly some facts
are unassailable.

12:04.659 --> 12:06.058
Do you know exactly
what happened

12:06.193 --> 12:07.860
on the night
the baby was reported missing,

12:07.995 --> 12:10.529
the precise sequence of events,

12:10.531 --> 12:12.131
who reported it,
who was there?

12:12.266 --> 12:15.000
Speak to this plainly
if you can.

12:15.136 --> 12:17.536
- Miss Howard,
the work we do at this hospital

12:17.672 --> 12:19.872
could not be accomplished
without the generosity

12:20.007 --> 12:22.074
of a great number
of very wealthy people.

12:22.209 --> 12:25.144
That said, we need
to be self-sustaining,

12:25.146 --> 12:28.147
so many of our staff
are simply ward girls.

12:28.149 --> 12:30.683
- Ward girls?
- Poor, destitute young women

12:30.818 --> 12:33.953
who, sadly, often lose
their infants in childbirth.

12:34.088 --> 12:37.156
They have nowhere else to go.

12:37.292 --> 12:39.158
But they are not
reliable witnesses.

12:39.294 --> 12:41.360
- If there are witnesses,
reliable or otherwise,

12:41.362 --> 12:42.962
then surely
there is also a report

12:43.097 --> 12:44.697
concerning what happened
that night.

12:44.832 --> 12:45.764
- There is no report.

12:45.900 --> 12:47.432
We doctors and nurses

12:47.434 --> 12:50.169
are imperfect servants
of the state, Miss Howard.

12:50.171 --> 12:53.105
However, tell me what it is
you want to see.

12:53.240 --> 12:55.774
There is nothing about our work
we want to hide.

12:55.776 --> 12:57.310
- In that case,

12:57.444 --> 13:00.445
I would very much like to see
Martha Napp's room.

13:00.581 --> 13:01.914
- Mm.

13:02.049 --> 13:04.984
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:04.986 --> 13:08.387
- Martha and her baby were
in this room on that night.

13:08.523 --> 13:10.990
- Who was she in a room with?

13:10.992 --> 13:13.058
- She was alone.
She had an infection.

13:13.060 --> 13:14.193
Had to be kept separate.

13:14.329 --> 13:16.595
- What kind of infection?
- Bowel.

13:16.597 --> 13:18.531
- Would this be
written down somewhere?

13:18.665 --> 13:20.666
There must be a file kept,
surely.

13:20.668 --> 13:21.466
Medical records.

13:21.468 --> 13:22.535
- I'm sure there would,

13:22.670 --> 13:24.069
but we can't be giving them out

13:24.071 --> 13:26.471
to every rag, tag, and bobtail.

13:26.473 --> 13:30.809
Why is this one asleep?
- Um, she lost some blood.

13:30.811 --> 13:33.412
- [gasps]
Were you not checking on her?

13:33.414 --> 13:35.414
She shouldn't sleep
if she's bleeding.

13:35.416 --> 13:39.151
You should know this.
So stupid, stupid, stupid.

13:39.286 --> 13:40.953
- Do you want me
to fetch a doctor, Matron?

13:41.088 --> 13:43.322
- No.
Stay here, I'll go.

13:46.627 --> 13:48.894
- Will she be--
- She'll be fine.

13:48.896 --> 13:50.029
Wake up.

13:51.165 --> 13:52.898
- May I ask you something,
nurse?

13:53.034 --> 13:54.499
- You can just call me Libby.

13:54.635 --> 13:56.335
- Did you know Martha Napp?

13:58.839 --> 14:00.839
Was this her room?

14:00.841 --> 14:04.777
- Um, it was when she came in.
- But?

14:04.912 --> 14:07.380
- But not the night
you're talking about.

14:08.649 --> 14:10.049
- If she's bleeding through
to the bed,

14:10.184 --> 14:11.917
she's not been properly packed.

14:12.053 --> 14:13.919
Matron, if you don't mind.

14:13.921 --> 14:16.321
- Libby, please show Miss
Howard to the waiting room.

14:16.457 --> 14:17.856
I will follow shortly.

14:17.992 --> 14:20.860
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

14:20.995 --> 14:23.262
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:23.398 --> 14:24.797
- Do you think
you can tell me about

14:24.932 --> 14:26.665
the maternal research wing?

14:26.801 --> 14:28.601
Is that where
Martha was kept that night?

14:28.736 --> 14:30.002
- No, no,

14:30.137 --> 14:32.271
she was in a room near
the recovery and postpartum,

14:32.407 --> 14:35.808
but the room, it won't
tell you anything, though.

14:35.943 --> 14:38.477
- But you will, won't you?

14:38.613 --> 14:43.282
- No.
No, I can't, I--

14:43.284 --> 14:47.019
I don't know what happened
to Martha's baby.

14:47.154 --> 14:48.220
None of us do.

14:48.355 --> 14:49.622
- No!
- Stop!

14:49.757 --> 14:50.956
- Be quiet.

14:50.958 --> 14:53.692
- Stop it!
- Colleen, Colleen, stop it.

14:53.694 --> 14:55.894
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:55.896 --> 14:58.497
- Be quiet!
- She won't let me de-louse.

14:58.499 --> 15:01.300
- You have a colony of
dirty lice living in your hair.

15:01.302 --> 15:02.835
How else will we rid of them?

15:02.970 --> 15:05.104
- We can chop your locks off
if you don't want to be washed.

15:05.239 --> 15:06.873
- Enough now, Colleen.

15:08.042 --> 15:10.709
This is not a sight
for your eyes, Miss Howard.

15:10.845 --> 15:13.312
Doubt you've ever been troubled
by head lice.

15:13.314 --> 15:14.847
- On the contrary.

15:14.982 --> 15:16.181
Growing up in the countryside,

15:16.317 --> 15:17.917
bugs, lice,
ticks of all manner

15:18.052 --> 15:19.852
were my constant companions,
Matron.

15:20.587 --> 15:21.920
- When you've finished
with this,

15:21.922 --> 15:24.723
Dr. Markoe needs to see you
in his office.

15:24.859 --> 15:26.125
- No.

15:26.127 --> 15:27.927
- Colleen,
you are to finish this,

15:28.062 --> 15:30.996
and then you are to go
to Dr. Markoe's office.

15:31.132 --> 15:32.798
- If she doesn't want
to go to the doctor's office,

15:32.933 --> 15:35.067
I'm quite certain
she shouldn't have to.

15:35.202 --> 15:38.203
- You are to go, now!

15:38.339 --> 15:45.444
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:53.988 --> 15:56.856
<i> [somber music]</i>

15:56.991 --> 16:04.163
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:06.133 --> 16:09.001
[wind whistling]

16:09.136 --> 16:16.242
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:27.621 --> 16:31.490
[thunder rumbling]

16:31.625 --> 16:38.297
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:38.432 --> 16:41.500
- It's so strange for
the child's stomach to be here,

16:41.635 --> 16:44.570
but for the poor creature
to already be buried.

16:44.706 --> 16:47.707
- It is merely science, Marcus.

16:47.841 --> 16:50.843
We are, after all,
only biological matter.

16:52.446 --> 16:56.115
- Yet...animated.

16:56.250 --> 16:58.450
With a soul

16:58.452 --> 16:59.585
and a conscience.

16:59.721 --> 17:02.654
[centrifuge rattling]

17:02.790 --> 17:06.325
<i> [soft suspenseful music]</i>

17:06.460 --> 17:08.528
Is something wrong?

17:08.662 --> 17:09.929
- No.

17:10.064 --> 17:16.936
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:23.077 --> 17:27.012
<i> [ominous music]</i>

17:27.014 --> 17:28.147
- I can't say for certain,

17:28.282 --> 17:31.083
but this looks
to be breast milk.

17:31.218 --> 17:35.020
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:35.022 --> 17:38.557
- Poison, powdered carbon...

17:38.692 --> 17:41.427
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:41.429 --> 17:43.295
- And breast milk.

17:43.431 --> 17:46.432
[indistinct chatter]

17:47.501 --> 17:48.901
[knocks on carriage]
- Come on.

17:53.975 --> 17:55.908
- Libby.

18:00.114 --> 18:02.381
Can I buy you lunch?

18:02.516 --> 18:05.418
I promise you can trust me.

18:07.521 --> 18:10.790
[indistinct chatter]

18:17.264 --> 18:20.032
I'm sorry if this is too...

18:21.803 --> 18:23.436
I'll have the menu du jour.

18:25.206 --> 18:26.738
- The same.

18:26.740 --> 18:29.341
And, um, may I have
a club soda?

18:29.477 --> 18:31.477
- The same.

18:34.482 --> 18:37.817
How is that woman?
The one who was bleeding?

18:37.951 --> 18:40.752
- Oh, Edith, yeah,
she's fine, yeah.

18:40.754 --> 18:42.488
They had to double douche her
to make it stop.

18:42.624 --> 18:44.790
There was nothing wrong
with her packing.

18:46.894 --> 18:50.295
Hot and cold douches
one after the other, you--

18:50.297 --> 18:51.764
you haven't had a baby, then?

18:54.168 --> 18:57.369
- No, I haven't.

18:57.371 --> 18:59.438
- Uh...

19:00.908 --> 19:02.608
Oh.

19:04.312 --> 19:05.678
- Is something wrong?

19:06.848 --> 19:10.382
- I--I was too nervous
to read the menu.

19:10.384 --> 19:12.384
- You don't like oysters?
- No.

19:12.386 --> 19:14.786
The city dumps all the horse
manure into the harbor.

19:14.922 --> 19:16.255
I believe it's why
they get so fat.

19:16.390 --> 19:17.589
- [chuckles]

19:17.725 --> 19:18.991
Waiter, can you please
take these away?

19:19.126 --> 19:20.392
- I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to...

19:20.528 --> 19:22.061
- Do you like pot pie?
- Mm.

19:22.196 --> 19:23.863
- Two baked beef pot pies.

19:23.998 --> 19:24.964
- Certainly.

19:26.934 --> 19:30.135
- I guess I know why you
invited me along for lunch,

19:30.137 --> 19:34.006
but to be honest,
I don't know very much.

19:34.008 --> 19:37.209
Nobody does,
and that's the truth.

19:37.345 --> 19:38.610
- Did someone
come to the hospital

19:38.612 --> 19:41.613
to ask you questions
about what happened?

19:41.615 --> 19:43.482
Did they write it down?
- Yeah.

19:43.617 --> 19:45.417
- So there could
be a report somewhere?

19:45.419 --> 19:46.819
- Yeah, yeah, I guess so.

19:49.957 --> 19:51.490
I don't imagine
I can go looking for it,

19:51.625 --> 19:53.025
if that's what
you're asking me.

19:53.027 --> 19:54.826
- No, Libby, I'm not asking you
to do anything

19:54.962 --> 19:56.495
that makes you
feel uncomfortable.

19:56.630 --> 19:57.897
- Think it takes long
for the pot pies?

19:58.032 --> 20:01.434
I'm afraid I only have
an hour for lunch.

20:02.570 --> 20:04.670
- We have a little time.

20:07.909 --> 20:09.542
- Is that your boyfriend?

20:10.512 --> 20:13.579
- No, no, it's my father.

20:13.715 --> 20:16.848
- Is he not around anymore?

20:16.850 --> 20:18.650
- No.

20:18.786 --> 20:21.453
He had an accident.
- What kind?

20:21.589 --> 20:24.456
<i> [tense music]</i>

20:24.592 --> 20:26.191
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:26.327 --> 20:30.062
- He had an accident
with a gun.

20:30.064 --> 20:31.863
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:31.865 --> 20:34.400
- An accident with a gun?

20:34.402 --> 20:37.669
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:37.671 --> 20:39.204
I know about
that sort of thing.

20:39.206 --> 20:42.808
M-my father, he...

20:42.944 --> 20:45.811
he had an accident too.

20:45.947 --> 20:49.348
With him,
it was a rope over a bridge.

20:49.483 --> 20:56.689
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:57.625 --> 20:59.892
- May I give you my card?
- Mm. [chuckles]

21:01.763 --> 21:03.629
- If you can feel
you can help me in any way.

21:03.631 --> 21:04.964
- Oh, yeah.

21:05.099 --> 21:07.967
Detective agency.
[chuckles] Wow.

21:08.102 --> 21:11.571
I will keep your card,
Miss Howard.

21:11.705 --> 21:13.773
But I'm not sure
I can help you.

21:26.320 --> 21:27.519
I'm sorry, I--

21:27.521 --> 21:29.121
- I understand, Libby.

21:29.256 --> 21:30.156
- Yeah.

21:32.460 --> 21:33.725
- It's just that I think

21:33.727 --> 21:35.461
the person that took
Martha Napp's baby

21:35.463 --> 21:37.129
has stolen another child.

21:37.131 --> 21:38.530
- Another child?

21:38.532 --> 21:41.200
- The infant daughter of
the Spanish consulate general

21:41.335 --> 21:42.201
and his wife.

21:42.336 --> 21:44.336
Señor and Señora Linares.

21:44.472 --> 21:47.206
I was told baby Ana was brought
to the Lying-In Hospital

21:47.341 --> 21:48.808
after a fall.

21:48.943 --> 21:50.676
- Yeah.

21:50.812 --> 21:53.479
Yeah, it was all pretty
hush-hush, as I remember,

21:53.481 --> 21:57.549
but uh,
the baby was discharged.

21:57.685 --> 21:59.384
- She was stolen from her home.

22:00.221 --> 22:02.154
Libby, was there anyone
at the hospital,

22:02.156 --> 22:05.757
a doctor or a nurse, who paid
the baby particular attention?

22:05.893 --> 22:08.027
- I don't--

22:08.162 --> 22:10.563
I don't want to get anybody
into trouble.

22:12.233 --> 22:15.701
Even if I do hate her.

22:15.837 --> 22:17.770
- The matron?

22:18.772 --> 22:19.939
- Yeah.

22:22.710 --> 22:26.045
Matron kept that baby
away from us all.

22:26.180 --> 22:28.314
She likes to think
she knows best,

22:28.316 --> 22:32.518
especially if the baby is from
a rich and powerful family.

22:32.654 --> 22:35.254
- Do you think the matron
would ever harm a baby?

22:35.389 --> 22:38.123
- Oh, no.

22:38.125 --> 22:40.326
No, I--

22:40.328 --> 22:45.531
I don't--I don't think
she'd ever hurt a child, no.

22:45.533 --> 22:47.300
- Do you know where she lives?

22:49.603 --> 22:52.672
[indistinct chatter]

22:56.277 --> 22:59.345
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

22:59.347 --> 23:06.319
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:19.901 --> 23:21.633
[clicking]

23:21.769 --> 23:24.636
- What are you doing?

23:24.638 --> 23:25.837
- I was going to knock,

23:25.973 --> 23:27.973
but I didn't want
to wake the child.

23:27.975 --> 23:30.910
- Marie doesn't have a child.

23:31.045 --> 23:33.913
- I'm on the board
of the Lying-In Hospital.

23:34.048 --> 23:36.382
Marie is a close confidante.

23:36.384 --> 23:40.786
- Well, she usually gets in
at around this time.

23:40.788 --> 23:42.755
- Have you ever heard a baby
in there?

23:44.325 --> 23:45.925
- Um...

23:46.060 --> 23:48.394
I know sometimes
she brings them home,

23:48.396 --> 23:51.531
but she hasn't done that
for quite a while.

23:51.665 --> 23:53.799
- When was the last time?

23:53.801 --> 23:56.135
- There was one.

23:56.270 --> 23:59.739
She lavished her
with attention.

23:59.873 --> 24:02.674
Had to give her back.

24:02.676 --> 24:04.744
It's sad, you see?

24:04.878 --> 24:07.546
She couldn't have her own.

24:07.681 --> 24:09.548
- [gasps softly]

24:09.683 --> 24:15.922
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:19.093 --> 24:21.961
- [humming softly]

24:22.096 --> 24:24.964
<i> [dissonant music]</i>

24:25.099 --> 24:32.171
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:39.313 --> 24:43.115
[humming softly]

24:43.117 --> 24:44.850
- I heard my baby cry.

24:44.986 --> 24:47.453
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:47.455 --> 24:51.657
- It was a dream, Helen.

24:51.659 --> 24:54.726
Look at the dress
Mr. Osgood sent.

24:54.862 --> 24:57.663
[gasps]
Isn't it beautiful?

24:57.665 --> 25:01.267
- [sobbing]
- Quiet.

25:01.402 --> 25:03.869
I hope you don't mind
I tried it on.

25:04.005 --> 25:06.606
[chuckles]

25:06.740 --> 25:09.208
- I don't want a goddamn dress.

25:09.343 --> 25:12.411
- [humming softly]
- [sobbing]

25:12.546 --> 25:15.414
<i> [ominous music]</i>

25:15.549 --> 25:18.718
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:22.690 --> 25:25.557
[baby crying]

25:25.693 --> 25:28.794
[telephone ringing]

25:43.044 --> 25:45.911
- I will not tolerate
further intrusions.

25:46.047 --> 25:49.048
Sara Howard has been here
prowling our halls.

25:49.183 --> 25:51.050
- Yours is a private
institution, Doctor.

25:51.185 --> 25:54.854
You're under no obligation
to entertain public scrutiny.

25:54.988 --> 25:57.523
- Miss Howard wasn't here
at my request.

25:57.525 --> 25:59.124
<i> [tense music]</i>

25:59.126 --> 26:01.861
What is our patronage for,
Mr. Byrnes,

26:01.995 --> 26:03.395
if you can't deter inquisitors

26:03.531 --> 26:05.931
who show up
at Laszlo Kreizler's bidding?

26:06.067 --> 26:07.733
- Kreizler is an egotist.

26:07.735 --> 26:09.869
Simply put,
I think he envies you.

26:10.004 --> 26:12.938
- This isn't a matter
of professional jealousy.

26:13.074 --> 26:15.807
Matron caught her snooping.

26:15.809 --> 26:18.744
<i> [tense music]</i>

26:18.880 --> 26:20.279
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:20.414 --> 26:22.214
I built this hospital
in the belief

26:22.350 --> 26:25.417
that medical science
could save women's lives,

26:25.553 --> 26:28.354
and our donors who share
my passion in this pursuit

26:28.356 --> 26:32.191
would object strongly to any
disclosure about this hospital.

26:33.294 --> 26:36.161
- Okay,
let me ask you this, then.

26:36.163 --> 26:37.897
Is there anything else
to unearth

26:38.032 --> 26:41.233
concerning the Martha Napp case

26:41.235 --> 26:44.503
that could connect you
to the Spanish baby?

26:44.638 --> 26:48.640
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:48.642 --> 26:50.510
- Of course not.

26:50.644 --> 26:52.444
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:52.580 --> 26:55.847
- Well, then you have nothing
to be concerned about.

26:55.849 --> 27:02.989
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:10.664 --> 27:13.198
[telephone rings]

27:13.200 --> 27:16.068
- John, wedding invite list,
my darling.

27:16.203 --> 27:19.539
You must tarry no longer.

27:19.673 --> 27:21.340
What are all these papers for?

27:21.475 --> 27:24.610
Is it something exciting
you're working on?

27:24.746 --> 27:27.479
- Well, yes,
as a matter of fact.

27:27.481 --> 27:29.281
They are the death certificates
of the babies

27:29.417 --> 27:31.083
from the Lying-In Hospital.

27:31.085 --> 27:32.684
There seems to be
an inordinately high number

27:32.820 --> 27:34.219
of mortalities there.

27:34.221 --> 27:36.688
- Please, John, don't tell me
such terrible things.

27:36.690 --> 27:38.958
I shall have nightmares.

27:39.093 --> 27:42.495
The wedding invite list?
- Yes.

27:43.965 --> 27:46.298
I see this
couldn't have waited?

27:46.434 --> 27:49.235
- Then I wouldn't get to see
where you write your stories.

27:54.776 --> 27:56.909
- [clears throat]

28:00.114 --> 28:01.246
- You've handed me a list

28:01.248 --> 28:04.183
of New York's
most eligible bachelors.

28:04.318 --> 28:07.453
I assume all of them will be
attending your party tomorrow?

28:07.455 --> 28:09.789
Except for Sara Howard,
of course.

28:09.923 --> 28:11.190
I see her name here.

28:11.325 --> 28:15.595
- Well, she's an eligible
bachelorette, I suppose.

28:15.729 --> 28:17.062
- Put her down for two,

28:17.064 --> 28:19.332
because of course
she'll bring someone.

28:23.537 --> 28:26.038
[knock at door]
- A moment, please.

28:27.141 --> 28:28.740
- I'll wait outside, Laszlo.

28:28.742 --> 28:29.875
- No, come in.

28:30.011 --> 28:31.611
We've just concluded
our session.

28:31.745 --> 28:36.081
Paulie, this is Sara Howard,
a friend of mine.

28:36.217 --> 28:38.150
- It's nice to meet you,
Paulie.

28:39.954 --> 28:41.921
- Please, sit down.

28:48.029 --> 28:51.497
<i> [delicate dramatic music]</i>

28:51.499 --> 28:58.471
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:00.842 --> 29:02.174
You want to try?

29:02.176 --> 29:09.181
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:09.183 --> 29:11.450
[chuckles]

29:11.585 --> 29:14.786
- Dr. Kreizler,
how'd you do that?

29:14.788 --> 29:16.588
- The mystery of magic.

29:16.724 --> 29:20.459
You, too, can learn it.
Run along.

29:20.594 --> 29:22.662
And Paulie,

29:22.796 --> 29:25.331
should you find a coin
in your pocket,

29:25.466 --> 29:28.467
buy yourself a deck of cards.

29:28.602 --> 29:34.941
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:42.816 --> 29:44.750
When the memories
of his childhood trauma

29:44.752 --> 29:46.018
threaten to overburden him,

29:46.020 --> 29:48.420
his mind shuts down.

29:48.422 --> 29:52.157
- He seems very attached.
- I've become very fond of him.

29:52.159 --> 29:54.159
- I interviewed Markoe
and his staff.

29:54.295 --> 29:56.095
- Did you find anything
about Martha?

29:56.230 --> 29:58.230
- Unfortunately, nothing
of great importance.

29:58.232 --> 30:00.366
But I did speak to someone
in confidence.

30:00.368 --> 30:02.634
- You believe she
could be assistance to us?

30:02.636 --> 30:03.835
- Perhaps.

30:03.971 --> 30:05.104
She has some suspicions about

30:05.239 --> 30:06.638
the matron
of the Lying-In Hospital,

30:06.774 --> 30:09.108
who certainly requires
further investigation,

30:09.243 --> 30:13.045
but she might merely
be an unpleasant character.

30:13.047 --> 30:15.515
- So we've reached an impasse.

30:15.649 --> 30:18.117
- Not quite.

30:18.252 --> 30:20.119
I spoke with Señora Linares.

30:20.254 --> 30:23.923
<i> [soft suspenseful music]</i>

30:24.058 --> 30:26.258
- Breathe.

30:26.260 --> 30:28.460
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:28.462 --> 30:30.262
Breathe.

30:30.264 --> 30:34.066
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:34.068 --> 30:36.268
Breathe.

30:36.270 --> 30:41.073
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:41.075 --> 30:43.542
Breathe.

30:43.677 --> 30:46.345
- Dr. Kreizler--
- Please, Señor.

30:46.480 --> 30:49.681
- I myself have been
placed under hypnosis by him.

30:49.817 --> 30:53.018
There is nothing to fear.

30:53.020 --> 30:55.687
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:55.689 --> 30:56.956
- Open your eyes.

30:57.091 --> 31:00.292
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

31:00.294 --> 31:07.299
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:07.301 --> 31:09.268
What do you see?

31:10.371 --> 31:11.303
- White.

31:11.439 --> 31:14.039
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:14.041 --> 31:16.241
The girls are in white.

31:16.243 --> 31:18.510
Dark hair.

31:18.646 --> 31:23.048
The walls, viridian green.

31:23.050 --> 31:26.318
The floor, Egyptian brown.

31:26.320 --> 31:30.255
A crimson flower in her hair.

31:30.257 --> 31:32.124
They are beautiful.

31:32.126 --> 31:34.660
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:34.796 --> 31:37.196
- You see a painting?

31:37.331 --> 31:39.465
- Yes.

31:39.600 --> 31:42.534
Edgar Degas.
"La Classe de danse."

31:42.670 --> 31:44.736
- It's in
the Metropolitan Museum.

31:44.738 --> 31:47.807
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:47.942 --> 31:50.275
- Turn away from the painting.

31:50.277 --> 31:53.545
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:53.547 --> 31:57.349
<i> [tense music]</i>
- [exhales deeply]

31:57.351 --> 32:04.156
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:06.227 --> 32:10.429
- [speaking Spanish]

32:10.564 --> 32:13.699
- What do you see?
- [speaking Spanish]

32:13.835 --> 32:15.167
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:15.302 --> 32:16.368
- Who do you see?

32:16.504 --> 32:18.970
- [panting]
- Who do you see?

32:18.972 --> 32:25.144
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:26.447 --> 32:28.814
- [speaking Spanish]

32:32.987 --> 32:36.122
[scraping, tapping]

32:36.256 --> 32:37.790
- Marcus?

32:37.792 --> 32:41.059
- This is the exact chemical
combination the killer used

32:41.195 --> 32:42.594
to make the antidote.

32:42.596 --> 32:45.131
I know it seems as if
it's only activated charcoal,

32:45.266 --> 32:46.799
but they added a tincture
of iodine.

32:46.934 --> 32:48.634
It's a thing of beauty.

32:50.204 --> 32:54.140
- Marcus, I--

32:54.275 --> 32:57.075
I did something horrible.

32:57.077 --> 32:59.545
- [chuckles]

32:59.680 --> 33:00.746
What'd you do?

33:00.881 --> 33:03.282
<i> [tense music]</i>

33:03.417 --> 33:06.618
- Byrnes came here
to see me one day.

33:06.620 --> 33:09.488
He asked what
we were working on.

33:09.490 --> 33:11.890
I told him about
the Linares case.

33:11.892 --> 33:17.964
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:18.098 --> 33:21.500
- [sighs]
Why?

33:21.502 --> 33:22.701
- He threatened you.

33:22.837 --> 33:24.837
He said he would
find some way

33:24.839 --> 33:26.104
to destroy you

33:26.106 --> 33:27.373
if I didn't give him
information.

33:27.508 --> 33:29.908
- What information?

33:30.044 --> 33:31.910
- About the Linares child.

33:31.912 --> 33:35.313
Don't tell Sara
or Dr. Kreizler, please.

33:35.315 --> 33:36.983
[stuttering]
I'm ashamed.

33:37.117 --> 33:39.318
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:39.453 --> 33:41.320
I'm sorry.

33:41.455 --> 33:45.491
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:47.127 --> 33:48.727
- So what happened, Laszlo?

33:48.863 --> 33:50.663
- Seems the experiment
was a failure.

33:50.665 --> 33:52.665
- I thought it was curious
how she was able

33:52.667 --> 33:55.201
to describe everything
so clearly, so vividly,

33:55.336 --> 33:57.870
as if she was--
- She's a painter.

33:58.006 --> 34:00.072
She was serious about it
until she got married.

34:00.208 --> 34:01.807
- She clearly sees things
in colors,

34:01.942 --> 34:04.810
but how does this help us
to recover her memories?

34:04.945 --> 34:08.915
- Well, perhaps
she could paint them?

34:13.087 --> 34:14.620
- There is some precedence
of this.

34:14.755 --> 34:16.488
- She almost fainted
during this session, I don't--

34:16.624 --> 34:19.025
- In the experiments of
Alfred Binet and Pierre Janet

34:19.159 --> 34:22.094
at the Sorbonne, their
subjects were given pencils

34:22.230 --> 34:25.564
to draw their visions while
in a somnambulistic state,

34:25.566 --> 34:27.900
and the renderings they
produced depicted memories

34:27.902 --> 34:29.835
they were unable to replicate
while awake.

34:29.970 --> 34:32.038
- Then we will need someone
to assist us.

34:32.172 --> 34:33.572
- Elizabeth did say that

34:33.708 --> 34:36.375
she and the Señora take classes
with Cecilia Beaux.

34:36.377 --> 34:38.044
Apparently,
they are quite close.

34:38.178 --> 34:40.312
- Wouldn't hurt to ask.

34:40.314 --> 34:42.848
- I adore the Señora.
Of course I do.

34:42.983 --> 34:46.852
She's the most wonderful
student of art,

34:46.987 --> 34:50.122
but it is an unusual
proposition, is it not?

34:50.258 --> 34:52.190
- I'll grant you that it is,
Cecilia,

34:52.192 --> 34:53.792
but we believe that
with your help,

34:53.794 --> 34:57.129
Señora Linares might be able
to remember that fateful day.

34:57.265 --> 34:58.597
- [sighs]
- And right now,

34:58.599 --> 35:01.400
it's our only hope
of saving the child.

35:01.402 --> 35:05.471
- I do believe that whenever
one paints or draws,

35:05.606 --> 35:08.607
one can enter
into a hypnotic state

35:08.609 --> 35:13.546
where you can penetrate
the realm of the imagination.

35:13.681 --> 35:15.681
- I am most grateful
for your assistance.

35:15.816 --> 35:17.616
The Señora knows you
as her teacher,

35:17.618 --> 35:19.217
and she trusts you.

35:19.219 --> 35:22.220
<i> [tense music]</i>

35:22.222 --> 35:25.291
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:25.426 --> 35:28.360
- Where are you now?

35:28.496 --> 35:31.898
- The Museum of Art.

35:32.032 --> 35:34.967
- Are you ready to leave it?

35:35.103 --> 35:38.237
- Yes.

35:38.372 --> 35:40.239
- Let's go outside, then.

35:40.374 --> 35:47.480
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:10.070 --> 36:13.472
<i> - Such vivid red.</i>

36:13.474 --> 36:15.474
Umbrella.

36:15.609 --> 36:19.077
- The Tea House.
- Yes.

36:19.079 --> 36:25.083
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:25.219 --> 36:27.153
- What do you see?

36:27.287 --> 36:29.155
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:29.289 --> 36:32.224
<i> - Something is watching me.</i>

36:32.226 --> 36:34.893
<i> I can sense it.</i>

36:34.895 --> 36:35.828
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:35.964 --> 36:37.563
- You got a dime, lady?
- [yelps]

36:37.698 --> 36:38.764
- For a sick soldier--
what served his country good.

36:38.899 --> 36:40.032
- Sorry.

36:40.168 --> 36:41.299
<i> - Does he frighten you?</i>

36:41.301 --> 36:43.369
- I'm afraid...

36:43.504 --> 36:45.103
but it's not him.

36:45.239 --> 36:48.374
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:48.509 --> 36:51.644
- Let's keep going, Isabelle.

36:51.646 --> 36:54.513
- It's watching me.

36:54.649 --> 36:56.314
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:56.316 --> 37:00.386
<i> I--I can feel the presence.</i>

37:00.521 --> 37:03.255
- The dark presence,
is it a woman?

37:03.257 --> 37:04.256
- Yes.

37:04.258 --> 37:08.060
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:08.062 --> 37:11.998
<i> She's close.</i>
<i> I feel it.</i>

37:12.132 --> 37:13.131
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:13.267 --> 37:17.135
I can...sense it.

37:17.137 --> 37:18.671
[flash lamp snaps, echoes]

37:18.806 --> 37:21.807
- What is it?
Describe it.

37:21.942 --> 37:25.811
[flash lamp snaps, echoes]
<i> - A flash, like a gunshot.</i>

37:25.946 --> 37:27.746
<i> I see her.</i>

37:27.882 --> 37:30.949
<i> My heart is beating so fast.</i>

37:30.951 --> 37:32.218
It's here.

37:32.353 --> 37:33.819
<i> She's here.</i>

37:35.623 --> 37:36.755
It's gone.

37:36.891 --> 37:39.958
<i> [soft ominous music]</i>

37:40.094 --> 37:46.999
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:51.572 --> 37:54.440
[birds chirping]

37:54.575 --> 37:56.943
- Señora saw someone suspicious
here.

38:03.784 --> 38:06.184
- Now look at the camera,
please.

38:06.320 --> 38:08.387
This might be a bit loud.

38:08.522 --> 38:10.056
[flash lamp snaps]

38:10.190 --> 38:12.525
- A flash like a gunshot.

38:13.994 --> 38:15.461
Milly, we'll need
to see anything

38:15.596 --> 38:18.064
that photographer's kept
from that day.

38:26.674 --> 38:29.141
- Miss Howard.
- Libby.

38:29.276 --> 38:31.677
What a pleasant surprise.

38:31.812 --> 38:33.679
You haven't been waiting
out here for me, have you?

38:33.814 --> 38:35.348
- Yes, but it's really
not a bother.

38:35.482 --> 38:40.219
I preferred to give you this
in person.

38:40.355 --> 38:41.620
- Is this the--
- Yeah.

38:41.756 --> 38:43.956
It's the report
of Martha Napp and her baby.

38:44.091 --> 38:45.490
I will need to put it back

38:45.492 --> 38:46.559
before anybody sees
that it's missing.

38:46.694 --> 38:48.093
- Of course.
- I must be going,

38:48.229 --> 38:50.363
but can I leave it with you
until tomorrow?

38:51.432 --> 38:52.565
- Thank you, Libby.

38:58.039 --> 39:01.106
[mysterious music playing]

39:01.108 --> 39:06.579
♪ ♪

39:06.714 --> 39:08.581
- Little Egypt works a lot
of bachelor parties,

39:08.716 --> 39:10.449
but she's not the original.

39:10.451 --> 39:12.517
Down at Mrs. Willoughby's
on the Bowery,

39:12.519 --> 39:15.388
she used to be known
as Connie Moretti

39:15.522 --> 39:17.390
of Mulberry Street.

39:17.524 --> 39:21.860
Boy, can she dance,
especially when she gets--

39:21.996 --> 39:24.529
- I think I might call it
a night, Oggie.

39:24.665 --> 39:26.531
- Oh, come on, John.
- Wait, wait, wait.

39:26.533 --> 39:28.067
- We're only just
getting started.

39:28.069 --> 39:29.935
- Did he just say he wanted
to call it a night?

39:30.071 --> 39:32.137
- On his own bachelor party.
- [scoffing] John.

39:32.273 --> 39:33.739
- Come on, maybe we could, uh,

39:33.874 --> 39:35.874
maybe we could slum it
somewhere and get a nightcap?

39:35.876 --> 39:37.743
- Come on.
- All right, all right.

39:37.878 --> 39:41.080
All right, but I get
to choose where we go.

39:41.082 --> 39:43.082
- That's more like it.
- [chuckles]

39:43.084 --> 39:46.018
[indistinct chatter]

39:46.153 --> 39:53.326
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:55.562 --> 39:59.031
- You seem uncommonly subdued,
John.

39:59.166 --> 40:02.501
What shall we toast?
You and Miss Violet?

40:02.637 --> 40:07.440
- A toast with water, no less.
[sighs]

40:07.574 --> 40:10.709
How about my grandmother?
- [chuckles]

40:10.711 --> 40:13.712
- Catherine Elizabeth
McAllister Moore.

40:13.848 --> 40:16.515
She, for one, would be very
happy that I was settling down

40:16.517 --> 40:19.718
with a woman such as V.

40:19.854 --> 40:22.922
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

40:23.057 --> 40:29.996
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:37.004 --> 40:37.904
Sara!

40:39.940 --> 40:41.541
Sara!

40:42.810 --> 40:44.743
- Keep your voice down.

40:44.745 --> 40:46.078
- Please come and join us.

40:46.213 --> 40:48.681
- I'm not coming to your
bachelor party, John Moore.

40:48.816 --> 40:50.615
- This part of the evening
is over.

40:50.617 --> 40:52.818
It'll be a more
intimate gathering

40:52.953 --> 40:54.620
of only John's closest friends.

40:54.755 --> 40:57.089
- It's far too late
and entirely inappropriate.

40:57.224 --> 41:01.026
- 'Tis now the very witching
time of night,

41:01.162 --> 41:04.563
when churchyards yawn
and Hell itself

41:04.565 --> 41:07.700
breathes out contagion
to this world.

41:07.835 --> 41:10.435
- Are you intoxicated, Laszlo?
Is he, John?

41:10.437 --> 41:11.770
- Lingonberry schnapps,

41:11.906 --> 41:14.106
and perhaps one or two glasses
of champagne.

41:14.241 --> 41:15.508
- Or three.

41:15.643 --> 41:16.976
- I still have my wits
about me, though.

41:17.111 --> 41:18.577
- Really, I don't--
- Please, Sara.

41:18.713 --> 41:19.979
I know my good friend
Oggie Gildersleeve

41:20.114 --> 41:23.950
would be sorely disappointed
by your absence.

41:25.452 --> 41:28.321
<i> [upbeat suspenseful music]</i>

41:28.455 --> 41:35.328
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:35.997 --> 41:37.663
- I have the file
on Martha Napp

41:37.665 --> 41:38.931
from the Lying-In Hospital.

41:39.066 --> 41:40.399
- So there is a file?

41:40.535 --> 41:42.735
- Says that the last person
to check on Martha Napp

41:42.870 --> 41:44.670
and her baby that night
was an employee

41:44.805 --> 41:46.339
named Colleen Ledwidge.

41:46.473 --> 41:48.073
I think the best plan is that

41:48.075 --> 41:50.275
someone goes into the
Lying-In Hospital undercover.

41:50.411 --> 41:53.078
- You?
- No, Bitsy.

41:53.214 --> 41:56.349
I would go myself,
but Markoe already knows me.

41:56.483 --> 41:57.816
- It seems poor Oggie

41:57.818 --> 41:59.552
will have no shortage
of company this evening.

41:59.687 --> 42:01.420
- Why, whatever do you mean,
John?

42:01.422 --> 42:02.888
- I imagine you are thinking

42:03.024 --> 42:04.757
a letter of recommendation
from the Gildersleeves

42:04.892 --> 42:07.159
about a former member of staff
would not go unheeded

42:07.294 --> 42:09.628
should she be seeking
future employment.

42:09.764 --> 42:12.565
I'm sure he'll do his utmost
to be of assistance.

42:12.700 --> 42:16.035
- [chuckles]
Where are we going, anyway?

42:16.037 --> 42:18.837
- [chuckles]

42:18.973 --> 42:22.241
[Cory Hall's "Glorious Rag"
playing]

42:22.377 --> 42:28.513
♪ ♪

42:28.649 --> 42:30.583
- Here's to your engagement,
John.

42:30.718 --> 42:31.717
Long time coming.

42:31.852 --> 42:33.586
[glasses clink]
- Cheers.

42:33.721 --> 42:35.854
- I hope she makes you happy.

42:35.856 --> 42:38.857
- Thank you, Cyrus.
She does.

42:38.859 --> 42:40.859
- Proud of you, old friend.
- [chuckles]

42:40.995 --> 42:43.262
I, uh,
I've been saving this for you.

42:43.398 --> 42:45.464
- Cyrus.

42:45.466 --> 42:46.799
Charta Riesling.

42:46.934 --> 42:49.668
- You stop by,
and it's here waiting for you.

42:49.804 --> 42:51.136
- I really
can't thank you enough.

42:51.138 --> 42:52.805
- I'm pleased to
have been of assistance,

42:52.940 --> 42:56.208
although it does seem
a highly unusual request.

42:56.343 --> 42:59.544
It all sounds rather, uh,
cloak-and-dagger.

42:59.546 --> 43:01.880
I know you won't tell me
the nature of your inquiries,

43:01.882 --> 43:04.683
but John did mention something
about research for him

43:04.685 --> 43:06.551
for an article
he plans to write.

43:06.687 --> 43:07.887
- For him?

43:08.022 --> 43:10.056
I'm working for him, am I?
- [chuckles]

43:10.958 --> 43:12.958
- Oh, whoa, whoa.
Easy.

43:13.094 --> 43:14.427
♪ ♪

43:14.561 --> 43:16.429
Thank you.
- You're welcome.

43:16.564 --> 43:18.764
♪ ♪

43:18.766 --> 43:20.165
Is he feeling okay?
- Lucious?

43:20.301 --> 43:24.237
Oh, yeah, he's fine.
This is a first for him.

43:24.371 --> 43:27.540
[indistinct chatter]

43:28.509 --> 43:29.842
You want to get some food?

43:29.977 --> 43:32.445
- Is Joanna still studying
the law, Cyrus?

43:32.579 --> 43:33.846
- [chuckles]

43:33.981 --> 43:36.849
Every minute of the day,
she's got her books out.

43:36.984 --> 43:38.050
Yeah,
but this isn't the best place

43:38.185 --> 43:39.785
for a young woman
to be working.

43:39.920 --> 43:42.255
- Did she not work
for the newspaper in Philly?

43:42.389 --> 43:43.856
- "Philadelphia Tribune."

43:43.991 --> 43:45.590
That's what she wants to do.

43:45.592 --> 43:47.059
She wants to write, get back
in the newspaper business.

43:47.194 --> 43:50.029
- Should I maybe ask
at the "Times"?

43:52.133 --> 43:55.734
- John.
That would be much appreciated.

43:55.736 --> 43:58.937
- Please excuse me
for a moment.

43:58.939 --> 44:03.276
- Um, may I call on you
for dinner sometime?

44:03.410 --> 44:05.544
♪ ♪

44:05.546 --> 44:07.480
- Yes, of course.

44:07.615 --> 44:09.482
[glass rings]

44:09.617 --> 44:13.352
[indistinct chatter]

44:13.354 --> 44:15.288
- [clears throat]

44:18.359 --> 44:20.092
[sighs]

44:20.227 --> 44:22.495
John Schuyler Moore
is getting married.

44:22.630 --> 44:25.564
[laughter and chatter]

44:25.566 --> 44:28.033
I had prepared notes,

44:28.169 --> 44:31.170
whimsical thoughts
on the nature of love.

44:31.172 --> 44:32.905
Practical counsel
in what it means

44:33.040 --> 44:35.640
to be united in body and soul
with another being.

44:35.642 --> 44:37.242
All that I had wanted to say,

44:37.378 --> 44:41.847
but now I realize I cannot
offer you any of these thoughts

44:41.849 --> 44:43.582
as I'm somewhat tipsy.

44:43.718 --> 44:45.584
[laughter and cheers]

44:45.720 --> 44:47.052
And it seems
I have left my notes

44:47.188 --> 44:48.654
in our previous establishment.

44:48.789 --> 44:51.891
[laughter]

44:52.860 --> 44:54.727
John...
[exhales deeply]

44:56.998 --> 45:00.265
It is my great privilege
to be your friend.

45:00.401 --> 45:02.067
And as Voltaire said,

45:02.069 --> 45:05.671
"Virtuous men alone
possess friends."

45:05.806 --> 45:08.607
You are indeed a virtuous man,

45:08.743 --> 45:12.477
a free spirit, restless soul,

45:12.613 --> 45:17.950
blessed with kindness,
bravery, and passion.

45:18.085 --> 45:20.819
You are sometimes reckless,

45:20.821 --> 45:23.889
certainly careless,

45:23.891 --> 45:25.157
and occasionally hopeless.

45:25.292 --> 45:27.159
[laughter]

45:27.294 --> 45:28.761
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:28.896 --> 45:30.696
But...
[clears throat]

45:30.831 --> 45:35.368
It is my sincerest hope, wish,

45:35.502 --> 45:39.238
that Violet sees you as we do,

45:39.374 --> 45:42.041
cares for you like we do,

45:42.176 --> 45:44.643
will know you
as we have known you,

45:44.645 --> 45:48.781
and will love you

45:48.916 --> 45:50.783
like we do.

45:50.918 --> 45:55.588
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:55.723 --> 45:57.390
Should she dare.

45:57.524 --> 45:59.324
[laughter]

45:59.460 --> 46:00.926
To John.

46:00.928 --> 46:03.062
all: To John.

46:03.064 --> 46:05.931
- Virtuous man!
[laughter]

46:05.933 --> 46:11.470
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

46:11.606 --> 46:14.473
<i> [ominous music]</i>

46:14.609 --> 46:21.747
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

46:23.484 --> 46:26.886
[baby crying]

46:27.021 --> 46:31.891
- [humming lullaby]

46:32.026 --> 46:34.893
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

46:34.895 --> 46:37.896
[humming and crying continue]

46:37.898 --> 46:45.071
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

46:46.641 --> 46:49.876
[baby crying]

46:52.247 --> 46:54.647
[gurgling]

46:54.782 --> 46:55.915
[crying stops]

46:58.119 --> 47:00.986
[humming]

47:00.988 --> 47:08.127
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
